{"TopicId":192318,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"Why Truss or Keel for spacestation?","CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T18:15:29Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T18:15:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne thing I notice in Mir 2 and Freedom is the usage of truss/keel structure. Clearly there are some physics that is IRL but not in KSP. May I ask why do they decide to go with a usage of truss/keel? And why are the newer designs forgoing such concept?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T18:21:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755213\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583950529\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 minutes ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOne thing I notice in Mir 2 and Freedom is the usage of truss/keel structure. Clearly there are some physics that is IRL but not in KSP. May I ask why do they decide to go with a usage of truss/keel? And why are the newer designs forgoing such concept?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat \u0022newer designs\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAnyway, trusses are very strong, stiff, and light, which is why they are the structure of choice for many applications.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T18:26:07Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755218\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583950894\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022137807\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022mikegarrison\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 minutes ago, mikegarrison said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWhat \u0022newer designs\u0022?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOPSEK (Russia), China Large Module Space Station (china), and various Commercial Space Station such as Axiom and etc. (US AFAIK have no plans for new space station)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Wjolcz","CreatedById":39636,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T19:59:06Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrusses are a pretty smart way of keeping important stuff away from the\u00A0 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E of docking spacecraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022800wm\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002265.00\u0022 height=\u0022520\u0022 width=\u0022800\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.sciencephoto.com/image/s6350053/800wm\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-11T20:01:46Z\u0022 title=\u002203/11/2020 08:01  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Wjolcz\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jestersage","CreatedById":165777,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T21:06:33Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755273\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583956746\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002239636\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Wjolcz\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Wjolcz said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTrusses are a pretty smart way of keeping important stuff away from the\u00A0 \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E of docking spacecraft.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u0026lt;picture of punctured solar panel\u0026gt;\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose holes are caused by \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"DDE","CreatedById":146349,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T21:12:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755297\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583960793\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n14 minutes ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThose holes are caused by \u003Cabbr title=\u0022Reaction Control System\u0022\u003ERCS\u003C/abbr\u003E thrusters?!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo. That would be a series of two collisions with Mir caused by an attempt to use remote-controlled unmanned docking of Progress ships to save money.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755221\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583951167\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nOPSEK (Russia)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRadiator and solar panel clearance. The truss is also gone from the later iterations of NEM:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022scale_1200\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002266.25\u0022 height=\u0022678\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://avatars.mds.yandex.net/get-zen_doc/1686199/pub_5db45adfa06eaf00b1485681_5db4d28d35ca3100b14db8a5/scale_1200\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755221\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583951167\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n2 hours ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nChina Large Module Space Station (china)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nLast I checked they are using a Mir 1 architecture with a Lyappa pivot on the core module, and no trusses at all.\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022original.jpg\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002269.77\u0022 height=\u0022714\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://mtdata.ru/u25/photoB977/20476800131-0/original.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u00221280px-RP1357_p165_Repositioning_Kvant_m\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002265.94\u0022 height=\u0022675\u0022 width=\u00221024\u0022 src=\u0022https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/50/RP1357_p165_Repositioning_Kvant_module_using_Lyappa_arm.svg/1280px-RP1357_p165_Repositioning_Kvant_module_using_Lyappa_arm.svg.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223755213\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022192318\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221583950529\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022165777\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Jestersage\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n3 hours ago, Jestersage said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMir 2\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSpacing for solar panels, solar-thermal turbogenerators, possibly even a nuclear reactor, experiment packages, and attitude thrusters (see the small trusses on Mir 1).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-11T21:20:07Z\u0022 title=\u002203/11/2020 09:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 11, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by DDE\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"magnemoe","CreatedById":57801,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-11T21:42:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPretty sure its to keep solar arrays and radiators away from activity like docking and spacewalks.\u00A0\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\nIt also let you orient solar panels and radiators for maximum effect / minimum drag pretty easy.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nThe Chinese station can not utilize their solar panels as well.\u00A0\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"mikegarrison","CreatedById":137807,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-12T02:30:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThese \u0022more recent\u0022 designs you mention are clearly less sophisticated and permanent than something like the ISS.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThe simplest stations were the original ones that were launched in one piece. Then came the stations where different modules were attached to a central hub. The ISS is the most sophisticated station people have built so far.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s obvious that if you don\u0027t have the capability to assemble/transport a large structure like the truss backbone of a major space station, then you do what you can by just adding bite-sized bits one by one. Much of the living/working space of the ISS was actually built by this latter method, but it all attaches to the main station infrastructure that is built around the central truss structure.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-12T02:34:16Z\u0022 title=\u002203/12/2020 02:34  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 12, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by mikegarrison\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"kerbiloid","CreatedById":129408,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-03-12T07:26:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey use because they can.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKSP can\u0027t because Unity doesn\u0027t allow loops without voodoo.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf Unity did, KSP stations would also use parallel truss structures to enforce the construction.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-03-12T07:26:30Z\u0022 title=\u002203/12/2020 07:26  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EMarch 12, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by kerbiloid\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}